As follow up for #7044 I would like to change the renderer of the completer to my custom subclass of it.

I tried `Completer.defaultRenderer = new myRenderer()` but `defaultRenderer` is const. This would be very easy to "fix", but might not be the most desirable option.

It seems reasonable that `ICompletionManager.register` should allow to swap the `Completer.IRenderer` implementation, as it is an option of `Completer` which is initialised by the `register()` method. However, currently, it is not possible to change the renderer:

https://github.com/jupyterlab/jupyterlab/blob/a51f9da32eb709ca2e305e1e5fd1b191778a3031/packages/completer-extension/src/index.ts#L90-L95

even though the options interface does allow to specify the renderer:

https://github.com/jupyterlab/jupyterlab/blob/a51f9da32eb709ca2e305e1e5fd1b191778a3031/packages/completer/src/widget.ts#L584-L602

this and the export of the `Renderer` class clearly suggests that the intent was to make the renderer customisable/subclassable in the extensions, but the implementation of the `ICompletionManager.register` prevents to.

### Suggested solution

Make the completer accept renderer: `Completer.IRenderer` and pass it to the `Completer` constructor, so:


```typescript
export interface ICompletionManager {
  register(
    completable: ICompletionManager.ICompletable,
    renderer: Completer.IRenderer
  ): ICompletionManager.ICompletableAttributes;
}
```

and

```typescript
return {
      register: (
        completable: ICompletionManager.ICompletable,
        renderer: Completer.IRenderer = Completer.defaultRenderer   // CHANGE
      ): ICompletionManager.ICompletableAttributes => {
        const { connector, editor, parent } = completable;
        const model = new CompleterModel();
        const completer = new Completer({ editor, model, renderer });   // CHANGE
        // ...
}
```

I can set up custom keyboard shortcuts just fine. However, it does not seem to work for `clear-all-cell-outputs` nor `clear-cell-output`.

Notably, the keyboard shortcut does not appear in the menu items list. Interestingly, it has (once?) appeared in the context menu (when right-clicking). I've tried different key mappings to rule out conflicts, e.g. H that I otherwise use for `hide-cell-outputs`. 

I have not managed to get this to work.

```
{
"shortcuts": [
        {
            "command": "notebook:hide-cell-outputs",
            "keys": [
                "H"
            ],
            "selector": ".jp-Notebook:focus"
        },
        {
            "command": "notebook:show-cell-outputs",
            "keys": [
                "Shift H"
            ],
            "selector": ".jp-Notebook:focus"
        },
        {
            "command": "clear-all-cell-outputs",
            "keys": [
                "Shift Backspace"
            ],
            "selector": ".jp-Notebook.focus"
        }

    ]
}
```
